title: Get emails about updates to GOV.UK

heading_context: Get emails about updates to GOV.UK
How to change your GOV.UK email subscriptions
chunks.html_content:
Some pages on GOV.UK have links to ‘get emails’.

You can get email updates about:

  • topics, for example ‘money’, ‘childcare’ or ‘education’
  • some individual pages
  • departments, agencies and public bodies
  • foreign travel advice
  • news and communications

You can also get emails about:

  • marine accident reports
  • railway accident reports

You can unsubscribe or make changes to your email subscriptions at any time.

You can also use the ‘unsubscribe’ or ‘change your email preferences’ links in the emails you get from GOV.UK to:

  • unsubscribe from some or all emails
  • change how often you get emails
  • change your email address

heading_context: Get emails about updates to GOV.UK
chunks.html_content:
If you’re having problems getting emails from GOV.UK, check your spam or junk folder.

If this does not work, contact GOV.UK support for help.
